# Pre-push verification

Before committing or pushing changes, run these commands locally and confirm they all pass:

```bash
pnpm run typecheck
pnpm run test:unit
pnpm run test:coverage
```

Do not push if any command fails. Fix failures first, then re-run the full sequence.

`test:coverage` enforces 100% thresholds (statements, branches, functions, lines) — treat any coverage regression as a blocker.

When tests involve WebSocket mocks or fake timers, prefer waiting for async side effects (e.g. `waitFor`) rather than assuming synchronous setup after render.
